definitions.definition: The chemical element ( symbol N) with an atomic number of 7 and atomic weight of 14.0067. It is a colorless and odorless gas.
Molecular nitrogen (N 2 ), a colorless , odorless gas at room temperature.
A specific nitrogen atom within a chemical formula , or a specific isotope of nitrogen.
examples: The two nitrogens are located next to one another on the ring.
